excerpt: Marine life shows, thrill rides, aquariums & up-close encounters with dolphins, penguins & more.
detail_description: SeaWorld Orlando is a renowned theme park in Orlando that offers an array of marine-themed attractions and shows. Visitors can enjoy thrilling rides like the Manta roller coaster and the Kraken Unleashed virtual reality roller coaster, as well as up-close encounters with dolphins, penguins, sea lions, and turtles. The park's killer whale show, One Ocean, provides insight into the majestic creatures' behaviors.
name: SeaWorld Orlando
address: 7007 Sea World Dr, Orlando, FL 32821, USA

excerpt: Venerable science center with hands-on exhibits & planetarium shows, plus giant-screen & 3-D films.
detail_description: The Orlando Science Center is a renowned destination offering an array of interactive experiences for visitors of all ages. From hands-on exhibits and planetarium shows to 3D films and towering dinosaur skeletons, the center provides an engaging exploration of science and technology. Guests can immerse themselves in four floors of interactive science exhibits covering topics such as weather, engineering, and space. Additionally, live animal encounters and special limited engagement exhibits add to the diverse offerings at the center. The Dr.
name: Orlando Science Center
address: 777 E Princeton St, Orlando, FL 32803, USA

excerpt: This 50-acre botanic garden & estate on Lake Rowena includes roses, camellias & a butterfly garden.
detail_description: Harry P. Leu Gardens is a 50-acre botanic garden and estate located on Lake Rowena, featuring a diverse array of flora including roses, camellias, cycads, azaleas, philodendrons, and bromeliads. The gardens offer free admission on the first Monday of every month from 9:00 am to 5:00 pm.
name: Harry P Leu Gardens
address: 1920 N Forest Ave, Orlando, FL 32803, USA

excerpt: Animal park with species such as alligators, birds & wild cats, plus educational shows & a zip line.
detail_description: Gatorland, known as the Alligator Capital of the World, is a renowned animal park in Orlando that focuses on reptiles. Spanning 110 acres, it is home to a diverse range of creatures including alligators, crocodiles, birds of prey, and other wildlife. Visitors can witness these fascinating animals up close and even enjoy educational shows and wildlife programs throughout the day.
name: Gatorland
address: 14501 S Orange Blossom Trl, Orlando, FL 32837, USA

excerpt: Sizable destination with an observation wheel, aquarium & wax museum, plus shops & restaurants.
detail_description: ICON Park is a large entertainment complex featuring an observation wheel, an aquarium, and a wax museum. The Orlando Eye, a 400-foot observation wheel located at ICON Park, offers stunning panoramic views of Orlando and its surroundings. The ride takes about 18 minutes and provides breathtaking vistas of natural lakes like Big Sandlake and Little Sandlake, as well as iconic landmarks such as Walt Disney World and Universal Orlando.
name: ICON Park

excerpt: All-inclusive park with dolphin encounters, snorkeling with rays, bird feeding & a lazy river.
detail_description: Discovery Cove is a serene escape from the hustle and bustle of popular Orlando theme parks. This all-inclusive park offers an exclusive opportunity to swim with dolphins, snorkel with thousands of tropical fish at The Grand Reef, and hand-feed exotic birds while learning about them from knowledgeable staff. It's a family-friendly destination where visitors can also enjoy a lazy river, bird feeding, and encounters with rays.
name: Discovery Cove
address: 6000 Discovery Cove Way, Orlando, FL 32821, USA

excerpt: Popular spot for walking, special events, feeding the swans & renting swan-shaped paddleboats.
detail_description: Lake Eola Park is a vibrant city centerpiece offering a variety of activities for both visitors and locals. From leisurely walks or jogs around the lake to feeding the diverse waterfowl, there's something for everyone. The park also hosts a Sunday farmer's market and special events, making it an ideal spot for relaxation and entertainment. Additionally, visitors can rent swan-shaped paddleboats to explore the lake.
name: Lake Eola Park
address: 512 E Washington St, Orlando, FL 32801, USA

excerpt: Complex with restaurants, bars, live shows & shops, including the world's largest Disney store.
detail_description: Disney Springs is a vibrant complex in Orlando that offers a diverse range of experiences, including restaurants, bars, live shows, and shops. It boasts the world's largest Disney store and features an array of dining options from award-winning chefs to casual eateries. The entertainment lineup includes outdoor live music and mainstream concerts at the House of Blues. Visitors can explore specialty boutiques, high-end fashion stores, and popular brand outlets for a full day of shopping.
name: Disney Springs
address: 1486 Buena Vista Dr, Lake Buena Vista, FL 32830, USA

excerpt: Attractions include roller coasters, kiddie rides & bumper cars plus go-karts & arcade games.
detail_description: Fun Spot America Theme Parks in Orlando offers a break from the typical big-name theme parks, providing a more old-fashioned and budget-friendly amusement park experience. With two convenient locations, it features thrilling rides like the White Lightning wooden roller coaster and Mine Blower indoor steel coaster. Families can enjoy bumper cars, go-karts, and a Ferris wheel. The park's free admission makes it an attractive option for those seeking affordable excitement in Orlando.
name: Fun Spot America
address: 5700 Fun Spot Wy, Orlando, FL 32819, USA

excerpt: Large, well-known theme park featuring movie-themed rides & shows, plus hotels & restaurants.
detail_description: Universal Orlando Resort is a renowned theme park that offers movie-themed rides, shows, hotels, and restaurants. The resort's Islands of Adventure park set a new standard for immersive experiences with the opening of the Wizarding World of Harry Potter Hogsmeade. Catering more to teens and young adults, Universal provides a grown-up ambiance.
name: Universal Orlando Resort

excerpt: Visiting exhibits join modern American graphics & African artifacts in a contemporary space.
detail_description: The Orlando Museum of Art offers a diverse and captivating experience for art enthusiasts. The museum showcases a wide array of exhibits, ranging from modern American graphics to African artifacts, creating a contemporary and thought-provoking atmosphere. With over 40,000 pieces in its collection, the museum features everything from ancient relics to avant-garde contemporary works by renowned American artists. Visitors can immerse themselves in workshops and classes offered by the museum, adding an interactive element to their visit.
name: Orlando Museum of Art
address: 2416 N Mills Ave, Orlando, FL 32803, USA

excerpt: Attraction with 100+ hands-on science exhibits plus laser tag, a ropes course & a 6D motion ride.
detail_description: WonderWorks Orlando is an amusement park for the mind located in the city's International Drive entertainment district. Housed in a unique upside-down building, it offers over 100 hands-on science exhibits across six wonder zones, including Extreme Weather, Space Discovery, and Physical Challenges. Visitors can also enjoy attractions like laser tag, a ropes course, and a 6D motion ride. The venue provides an engaging and educational experience suitable for all ages.
name: WonderWorks Orlando

detail_description: Crayola Experience Orlando, located in The Florida Mall, is a vibrant indoor destination that offers an array of colorful and creative activities for children. With nearly 30 hands-on attractions, kids can engage in art projects, entertaining shows, and interactive experiences. From making drip art to creating souvenirs out of crayon wax, there are plenty of opportunities for young ones to unleash their creativity.
name: Crayola Experience Orlando
address: 8001 S Orange Blossom Trl, Orlando, FL 32809, USA

excerpt: Famous, sprawling amusement park featuring movie-themed rides, attractions & entertainment.
detail_description: Universal Studios Florida is a sprawling amusement park in Orlando that offers an immersive experience into the world of Hollywood entertainment. The park features movie-themed rides, attractions, and entertainment that cater to visitors of all ages. From family-friendly adventures like Despicable Minion Mayhem to high-speed coasters like Hollywood Rip Ride Rockit and Revenge of the Mummy, there's something for everyone.
name: Universal Studios Florida

excerpt: Family-friendly exhibits with a variety of sea creatures (most offer play areas & group packages).
detail_description: SEA LIFE Orlando Aquarium, located in the heart of Orlando's tourist district at ICON Park, is a family-friendly attraction featuring over 5,000 sea creatures from around the world. The aquarium offers indoor and outdoor exhibits, including a unique 360-degree underwater tunnel for an immersive experience with marine life. Visitors can expect state-of-the-art showcases and interactive opportunities to view and touch various sea creatures. Additionally, SEA LIFE Orlando Aquarium provides group packages and play areas for families.
name: SEA LIFE Orlando Aquarium

detail_description: The Kennedy Space Center Store is a must-visit destination for space enthusiasts and curious minds alike. Located in Cape Canaveral, just a short drive from Orlando, this iconic attraction offers interactive exhibits, simulators, IMAX movies, and special events that cater to both kids and adults. Visitors have the opportunity to learn about the history of space exploration and current missions through hands-on experiences. Additionally, the center provides the chance to witness rocket launches, meet astronauts, and participate in unique events.
name: Kennedy Space Center Store
address: 9339 Jeff Fuqua Blvd, Orlando, FL 32827, USA

excerpt: Historic, family-friendly museum featuring extensive Tiffany collection & special exhibits.
detail_description: The Charles Hosmer Morse Museum of American Art is a historic and family-friendly museum located in Orlando, Florida. While the city is known for its theme parks, it also offers a diverse selection of cultural institutions. The museum, established in 1995 but with roots dating back to 1942, houses an extensive collection of Tiffany treasures acquired from the estate of Louis Comfort Tiffany.
name: The Charles Hosmer Morse Museum of American Art
address: 445 N Park Ave, Winter Park, FL 32789, USA

excerpt: Museum with kitschy oddities on display, including shrunken human heads & rare animal skeletons.
detail_description: Ripley's Believe It or Not! in Orlando is a must-visit museum for those intrigued by the bizarre and extraordinary. The collection features peculiar oddities such as shrunken human heads and rare animal skeletons. Visitors can compare themselves to a replica of the tallest man in the world and explore interactive exhibits showcasing fascinating facts from around the globe. Unlike many other museums, Ripley's stays open until late, making it an excellent nighttime activity in Orlando.
name: Ripley's Believe It or Not!

excerpt: Teams use problem-solving skills in immersive room sets like a prison cell & an imperiled spaceship.
detail_description: At The Escape Game Orlando, adventure awaits as you and your team dive into a world of immersive escape rooms. Choose from an array of captivating themes, such as a 1950s prison cell or a perilous spaceship, and embark on a thrilling mission to solve puzzles and uncover clues within just 60 minutes. This experience is perfect for families, friends, couples, or corporate groups seeking an engaging way to bond while testing their problem-solving skills.
name: The Escape Game Orlando

excerpt: Extreme thrill rides & the Wizarding World of Harry Potter attract crowds to this Universal park.
detail_description: Universal Islands of Adventure is a top destination for thrill-seekers and fans of the Wizarding World of Harry Potter. The park features iconic attractions like Hogwarts Castle in the Wizarding World's Hogsmeade, family-friendly areas like Seuss Landing, and classic rides such as Jurassic Park. Visitors can experience innovative thrills on Spiderman and Skull Island: Reign of Kong. One standout attraction is Hagrid's Magical Creatures Motorbike Adventure, offering a unique story coaster experience.
name: Universal Islands of Adventure

excerpt: Winter Park is a city near Orlando, Florida. Its known for its abundant outdoor spaces like leafy Central Park. The Charles Hosmer Morse Museum of American Art showcases glass art by Louis Comfort Tiffany. Overlooking Lake Osceola, the Albin Polasek Museum & Sculpture Gardens displays works by the notable Czech-American artist. By Lake Virginia, Cornell Fine Arts Museum shows antiquities and contemporary works.
detail_description: Winter Park, located near Orlando, Florida, is a picturesque city with abundant outdoor spaces and cultural attractions. The Charles Hosmer Morse Museum of American Art showcases glass art by Louis Comfort Tiffany while the Albin Polasek Museum & Sculpture Gardens displays works by the notable Czech-American artist. Additionally, Cornell Fine Arts Museum exhibits antiquities and contemporary works.
name: Winter Park

excerpt: Museum chain for life-size wax replicas of famous Americans & historic icons in themed galleries.
detail_description: Madame Tussauds Orlando is a popular wax museum located near the iconic wheel in Orlando. The museum features lifelike wax replicas of famous Americans and historic icons displayed in themed galleries. Visitors can expect an impressive collection of meticulously crafted waxworks, representing well-known personalities from various fields. From modern music icons to historical figures, superheroes, and sports legends, the museum offers interactive encounters with intricately crafted figures set in themed environments.
name: Madame Tussauds Orlando

excerpt: Energetic attraction at Universal Orlando featuring a variety of restaurants, shops & family shows.
detail_description: Universal CityWalk Orlando is a vibrant attraction within the Universal Orlando Resort, offering an array of entertainment options for visitors. The complex features a diverse range of restaurants, shops, and family-friendly shows. From themed games like Great Movie Escape to clubs, cinemas, and mini-golf, there's something for everyone. Indulge in outrageous milkshakes and desserts at The Toothsome Chocolate Emporium or savor sushi-burger fusion at The Cowfish.
name: Universal CityWalk Orlando

excerpt: This museum dedicated to the Titanic offers artifacts, re-creations of the ship & guided tours.
detail_description: Step back in time and immerse yourself in the tragic story of the Titanic at "Titanic: The Artifact Exhibition." This museum showcases over 300 original artifacts recovered from the wreck site, along with full-scale room recreations and costumed actors that bring history to life. Upon entry, guests receive a replica boarding pass and embark on a chronological journey through the ship's life.
name: Titanic: The Artifact Exhibition

detail_description: The Winter Park Scenic Boat Tour offers a unique and historic experience as visitors embark on 18-passenger pontoon boats to explore the picturesque Winter Park Chain of Lakes. The tour provides an opportunity to admire the beautiful homes surrounding Kraft Azalea Gardens and witness local flora, fauna, and even occasional wildlife like fish, birds, and alligators. Knowledgeable guides lead the one-hour cruise through scenic canals while sharing insights into historical landmarks and natural wonders.
name: Scenic Boat Tour
address: 312 E Morse Blvd, Winter Park, FL 32789, USA

excerpt: Water park featuring slides & a kids' splash area, plus a swimming area with oceanlike swells.
detail_description: Disney's Typhoon Lagoon Water Park is a thrilling destination for families and adventure seekers alike. The park offers a variety of attractions, including slides, a kids' splash area, and a swimming area with ocean-like swells. Visitors can dive into the wreckage of a fictional whirlwind storm and enjoy raft rides like the 400-foot water coaster or the exhilarating Humunga Kowabunga slide.
name: Disney's Typhoon Lagoon Water Park

detail_description: iFLY Indoor Skydiving in Orlando offers an exhilarating simulated skydiving experience for all ages, with no prior experience required. The state-of-the-art vertical wind tunnel technology provides a safe environment for participants to feel the thrill of free-fall without the need to jump from an airplane. With expert instructors and provided equipment including flight suits, helmets, and goggles, visitors can enjoy the sensation of flying while learning new skills.
name: iFLY Indoor Skydiving - Orlando

detail_description: Located at ICON Park, the Museum of Illusions Orlando is a popular attraction featuring over 50 mind-bending illusions, tricks, and riddles. Visitors can explore exhibits that defy gravity, create optical illusions, and offer unique photo opportunities. The museum offers interactive experiences for all ages and is conveniently situated near other attractions. It's a place where visitors can immerse themselves in a world of wonder and enjoy creative ways to challenge their perception of reality through various exhibits that are both entertaining and educational.
name: Museum of Illusions Orlando
address: 8375 International Drive Icon Park, FREE PARKING GARAGE: Floors 4-7, 8367 International Dr Suite #250, Orlando, FL 32819, USA

excerpt: Large, multilevel performing arts venue showcasing Broadway plays, concerts & dance performances.
detail_description: The Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts is a grand, multilevel venue that offers a wide array of performances including Broadway plays, concerts, and dance shows. Upon entering the center, visitors are greeted by a magnificent staircase and ambient lighting that sets the stage for an immersive arts experience.
name: Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts
address: 445 S Magnolia Ave, Orlando, FL 32801, USA

excerpt: Whimsical chocolate museum & factory offering fantasy-themed tours, custom bars & other sweet eats.
detail_description: Embark on an enchanting adventure at Chocolate Kingdom - Factory Adventure Tour, a whimsical chocolate museum and factory in Orlando. This interactive experience allows visitors to witness the transformation of cocoa into delectable chocolate treats through exhibits like the Mystical River of Chocolate and a Micro Batch Bean-to-Bar room.
name: Chocolate Kingdom - Factory Adventure Tour

detail_description: An escape room center called "Escapology" is located in Orlando and it's popular with couples because it's a great way to spend some time together. The rooms are challenging and the staff is friendly, which makes the experience even more fun. At the end of each game, the players are given a water bottle and a bracelet as souvenirs.
name: Escapology Escape Rooms Orlando
address: 11951 International Dr c3, Orlando, FL 32821, USA

excerpt: Water-based center with an inflatable aqua park, wakeboarding, ropes courses & climbing walls.
detail_description: Nona Adventure Park, located in the Lake Nona area of Orlando, offers a unique water-based experience with its inflatable aqua park and wakeboarding course. The aqua park features a large obstacle-filled course for visitors to float and have fun. Additionally, the cable park provides an exciting wakeboarding experience through a pulley system.
name: Nona Adventure Park

excerpt: Bustling urban thoroughfare lined with numerous eateries, boutiques, gift shops & amusement parks.
detail_description: International Drive, also known as -Drive, is a vibrant 11-mile stretch in Orlando that offers a plethora of entertainment, dining, and shopping options. It's home to the Orange County Convention Center and Orlando's Official Visitor Center. Visitors can explore an array of attractions such as amusement parks, indoor skydiving at iFLY Orlando, NASCAR-themed experiences at -Drive NASCAR, and interactive exhibits at WonderWorks.
name: International Dr

excerpt: County park with a butterfly garden, interpretive trails & nature center with educational programs.
detail_description: Tibet-Butler Nature Preserve is a 440-acre wildlife sanctuary in Orlando, offering gentle interpretive trails through various habitats. Families can enjoy the serene natural surroundings and spot diverse animals along the paths. The on-site nature center features educational exhibits, a butterfly garden, and a tortoise sanctuary.
name: Tibet-Butler Nature Preserve
address: 8777 Winter Garden Vineland Rd, Orlando, FL 32836, USA

excerpt: Ride with double-seat swings, offering views from 450 feet up & drinks at a street-level bar.
detail_description: The Orlando Starflyer is a thrilling swing ride that takes you 450 feet up in the air, offering breathtaking 360-degree views of the surrounding area. With double-seat swings and speeds reaching up to 45 miles per hour, this towering attraction promises an unforgettable experience. Located near Ripleys and Sleuths Mystery Dinner Shows on -Drive, it's a perfect addition to any evening at ICON Park.
name: Orlando Starflyer
address: 8265 International Dr unit c suite 108, Orlando, FL 32819, USA

detail_description: The Mall at Millenia is home to a variety of dining options, from casual buffets to more upscale restaurants like PF Changs. Whether you're in the mood for a diverse buffet or a high-end dining experience, this shopping center has something for every palate.
name: Millenia

excerpt: This kid-friendly dinner drama with acrobatics & music takes place on an 18th-century ship replica.
detail_description: Set sail for an unforgettable evening at Pirates Dinner Adventure, where family-friendly fun meets thrilling entertainment aboard a stunning 18th-century ship replica. This captivating dinner show features acrobatic pirates swinging from the sails, engaging music, and a delightful mystery to unravelespecially festive during the holiday season! Guests can indulge in a delicious three-course meal while enjoying unlimited soft drinks and wine options for adults.
name: Pirates Dinner Adventure

excerpt: Indoor fun center featuring go karts, racing simulators, VR games, laser tag, bowling & dining.
detail_description: Andretti Indoor Karting & Games Orlando is a top-notch entertainment facility that offers a wide range of activities for visitors. Named after racing legend Mario Andretti, this 150,000-square-foot venue features indoor karting, boutique bowling, arcade games, laser tag, virtual reality experiences, and an extreme ropes course with curved ziplines. The pro racing simulators provide an immersive experience with motion effects and tension in the seatbelt to simulate real race conditions.
name: Andretti Indoor Karting & Games Orlando

excerpt: Pirate-themed mini-golf chain with 18-hole, landscaped courses set among waterfalls & caves.
detail_description: Pirate's Cove Adventure Golf in Orlando, Florida is a must-visit for golf enthusiasts. The venue offers two 18-hole courses with unique challenges and lush tropical vegetation to shield players from the sun. The affordably priced attraction features cascading waterfalls, dungeons, tropical flora, and even an actual pirate ship to putt through. Visitors rave about the beautifully designed amenities, including mermaids and numerous water features throughout the intricately themed mini-golf course.
name: Pirate's Cove Adventure Golf

excerpt: Outdoor, pedestrian-friendly mall with name-brand shops & restaurants plus 20-screen cinema & bars.
detail_description: Pointe Orlando is an outdoor mall located in a pedestrian-friendly area, offering a variety of name-brand shops, restaurants, and entertainment options. The venue features popular dining establishments such as Cuba Libre Restaurant & Rum Bar, Marlow's Tavern, Ra Sushi, Oceanaire Seafood Room, and Taverna Opa.
name: Pointe Orlando

excerpt: Tony Brent tackles magic tricks & improv during this interactive act paired with casual eats.
detail_description: Experience an unforgettable evening at the Outta Control Dinner Show in Orlando, Florida. This interactive comedy and magic performance by Tony Brent will leave you amazed and entertained. With 24 years of experience, Tony's spellbinding tricks and improv skills will keep you engaged throughout the show. The inclusive nature of the performance ensures that both adults and kids are involved, making it a perfect family-friendly entertainment option.
name: The Outta Control Magic Comedy Dinner Show

excerpt: Indoor recreation center with a bowling alley, glow-in-the-dark minigolf & go-karts, plus a cinema.
detail_description: Dezerland Park Orlando is an expansive indoor entertainment center that offers a wide range of activities to keep visitors entertained all day long. With over 800,000 square feet of space, the park features go-kart racing, bowling, axe-throwing, trampoline jumping, arcade games, bumper cars, and glow-in-the-dark mini-golf. Additionally, it houses Orlando's largest museum - The Auto Museum.
name: Dezerland Park Orlando

detail_description: This cirque is an amazing performance with breathtaking architecture and feats of athleticism that will leave you awestruck. The show runs every day from 6 PM to 9 PM and does not fail to leave its visitors in amazement multiple times during its duration.
name: Drawn to Life presented by Cirque du Soleil & Disney
address: 1478 Buena Vista Dr, Lake Buena Vista, FL 32830, USA

detail_description: Orlando International Premium Outlets, formerly known as Prime Outlet, is a shopping paradise in Orlando. It boasts over 125 popular brands including HUGO BOSS Factory Store, Tumi, Converse, and Neiman Marcus LAST CALL. With 16 dining options spread across its 700,000 square feet of space, visitors can refuel at places like Pinkberry before exploring more shops or enjoying the zillion eateries nearby.
name: Orlando International Premium Outlets

excerpt: Recreation of famed Harry Potter street, with wand shop & ride based on goblin-owned Gringotts Bank.
detail_description: The Wizarding World of Harry Potter - Diagon Alley is a magical recreation of the famous street from the Harry Potter series, featuring a wand shop and a thrilling ride based on Gringotts Bank. This enchanting area at Universal Studios Florida offers an immersive experience for fans of the beloved books and films. Visitors can explore intricately detailed shops, such as Zonkos Joke Shop and Honeydukes Sweetshop, before indulging in themed treats and drinks like butterbeer.
name: The Wizarding World of Harry Potter - Diagon Alley

excerpt: Amusement park featuring old-time carnival rides, shopping, dining & weekly classic car shows.
detail_description: Old Town is a 1950s-style open-air attraction that spans across 10 acres, offering classic amusement park rides, live entertainment, and over 75 specialty shops. With its boardwalk-style streets, it provides an authentically Floridian theme park experience. Visitors can enjoy dining at one of the eight restaurants or take part in the Saturday Nite Car Cruise featuring over 300 classic cars. Additionally, there are weekly car shows on Fridays showcasing a variety of vehicles.
name: Old Town
address: 5770 W Irlo Bronson Memorial Hwy, Kissimmee, FL 34746, USA

excerpt: 5-story museum focused on the history of Central Florida, with some interactive exhibits.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of downtown Orlando, the Orange County Regional History Center is a captivating 5-story museum that invites visitors to explore Central Florida's rich and diverse history. Housed in a beautifully restored historic courthouse, this Smithsonian-affiliated gem offers an engaging journey through time, showcasing everything from prehistoric eras to modern-day life. With interactive exhibits designed for all ages and detailed dioramas illustrating daily life throughout the years, its an ideal spot for families looking to learn while having fun.
name: Orange County Regional History Center
address: 65 E Central Blvd, Orlando, FL 32801, USA

excerpt: Small museum dedicated to American art, with a lakeside sculpture garden on its manicured grounds.
detail_description: The Mennello Museum of American Art, located in Orlando and owned by the city, was established in 1998 to showcase a remarkable collection of Earl Cunningham's paintings. The museum hosts temporary exhibitions and educational programs while also offering free access to the Marilyn L. Mennello Sculpture Garden, known for its impressive live oak tree called The Mayor.
name: Mennello Museum of American Art
address: 900 E Princeton St, Orlando, FL 32803, USA

excerpt: Marine life shows, waterslides, aquariums & up-close encounters with dolphins, penguins & more.
detail_description: Aquatica Orlando, nestled within the SeaWorld grounds, is a sprawling water park that offers an array of aquatic attractions for visitors of all ages. With 42 slides, rivers, and lagoons spread across 59 acres, it stands as one of Florida's largest water parks. The park's thematic design reflects the southern Pacific region and features body slides, raft slides, lazy rivers, wave pools, and splash zones for kids.
name: Aquatica Orlando
address: 5800 Water Play Way, Orlando, FL 32821, USA

excerpt: Celebration is a master-planned community and census-designated place in Osceola County, Florida, United States. A suburb of Orlando, Celebration is located near Walt Disney World Resort and was originally developed by The Walt Disney Company. Its population was recorded as 11,178 in the 2020 United States census. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Celebration is a charming community located in Osceola County, Florida, near the Walt Disney World Resort. Developed by The Walt Disney Company, it features wide streets and colorful shops and houses that make for a lovely day of wandering. The area offers a variety of dining options, including the iconic Columbia Restaurant on Front Street and the Bohemian Hotel Celebration's Lakeside Bar + Grill.
name: Celebration
